<span id="ix.cccxlvii-p1"></span> <span class="c18"><span
id="ix.cccxlvii-p1.1"></span>Letter CCCLII.</span>

<span id="ix.cccxlvii-p2"></span>Libanius to Basil.

<span id="ix.cccxlvii-p3"></span><span class="c14"><span
id="ix.cccxlvii-p3.1"></span>Behold</span>!  I have sent you my speech,
all streaming with sweat as I am!  How should I be otherwise, when
sending my speech to one who by his skill in oratory is able to shew
that the wisdom of Plato and the ability of Demosthenes were belauded in
vain?  I feel like a gnat compared with an elephant.  How I shiver and
shake, as I reckon up the day when you will inspect my performance I am
almost out of my wits!

